1
00:00:02,999 --> 00:00:06,268
Captain's Personal Log,
Stardate 51247.5.

2
00:00:06,306 --> 00:00:09,677
It's been a week since
our return to Deep Space 9

3
00:00:09,713 --> 00:00:12,150
but the mood
of celebration continues.

4
00:00:12,185 --> 00:00:14,155
We're still at war,
and the station's

5
00:00:14,189 --> 00:00:16,490
been designated headquarters
for the Ninth Fleet.

6
00:00:16,528 --> 00:00:18,589
That, plus
our strategic position

7
00:00:18,632 --> 00:00:20,728
guarding the wormhole,
makes DS9

8
00:00:20,771 --> 00:00:22,468
one of the most
tempting targets

9
00:00:22,508 --> 00:00:24,034
in the entire quadrant.

10
00:00:24,078 --> 00:00:28,315
But for now, at least,
the war seems very far away.

11
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:35,727
- Morning.
- Good morning.

12
00:00:35,770 --> 00:00:37,399
Good morning.

13
00:00:37,441 --> 00:00:38,910
Morning, Major.

14
00:00:38,944 --> 00:00:40,641
Good morning, Captain.

15
00:00:40,681 --> 00:00:43,677
Do you know how much I missed
hearing you say that?

16
00:00:43,721 --> 00:00:45,748
Do you know how much
I hated saying

17
00:00:45,792 --> 00:00:47,056
"Good morning, Dukat"?

18
00:00:47,095 --> 00:00:48,063
I can imagine.

19
00:00:48,098 --> 00:00:49,431
What's on the agenda?

20
00:00:49,467 --> 00:00:52,098
USS <i>Potemkin</i>
has completed her repairs

21
00:00:52,139 --> 00:00:54,406
and is rejoining the fleet
later today.

22
00:00:54,444 --> 00:00:56,175
<i>Exeter, Sutherland</i> and <i>Agaki</i>

23
00:00:56,215 --> 00:00:58,117
have submitted
resupply requests

24
00:00:58,153 --> 00:01:00,454
and there are
about 1,000 messages

25
00:01:00,492 --> 00:01:01,756
from Starfleet Command

26
00:01:01,794 --> 00:01:03,855
awaiting your "eyes-only"
attention.

27
00:01:03,899 --> 00:01:05,026
Anything else?

28
00:01:05,068 --> 00:01:07,403
General Martok is waiting
in your office.

29
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:09,239
Oh, I'll start with the General.

30
00:01:09,344 --> 00:01:10,779
I thought you would.

31
00:01:12,551 --> 00:01:16,583
Have I mentioned
that it's good to be home?

32
00:01:16,627 --> 00:01:18,324
Once or twice.

33
00:01:20,334 --> 00:01:22,133
All right.

34
00:01:26,181 --> 00:01:28,014
You knew about this, didn't you?

35
00:01:28,052 --> 00:01:30,182
Oh, I had a pretty good idea.

36
00:01:30,223 --> 00:01:33,219
And you did nothing to stop it.

37
00:01:33,263 --> 00:01:34,857
No.

38
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:37,303
In fact, I recommended you
for the position myself.

39
00:01:37,406 --> 00:01:40,071
Allow me to offer
my congratulations

40
00:01:40,111 --> 00:01:43,676
to the new Supreme Commander
of the Ninth Fleet.

41
00:01:43,719 --> 00:01:46,623
Do you have any idea
how much paperwork

42
00:01:46,659 --> 00:01:49,290
a Supreme Commander has to do?

43
00:01:49,332 --> 00:01:50,425
You're welcome.

44
00:01:52,137 --> 00:01:54,574
May I arrange quarters
for you on the station?

45
00:01:54,610 --> 00:01:56,979
No, I'll keep my flag
aboard the <i>Rotarran.</i>

46
00:01:57,015 --> 00:01:58,484
It may be cramped

47
00:01:58,519 --> 00:02:01,583
but at least I'll feel
like I'm still in the war.

48
00:02:01,626 --> 00:02:04,427
By the way, I'd like Worf
to continue functioning

49
00:02:04,465 --> 00:02:06,595
as my principal
Intelligence Officer.

50
00:02:06,637 --> 00:02:08,470
I don't see any problem
with that.

51
00:02:08,507 --> 00:02:11,810
He's the only officer I know
who can never get enough work.

52
00:02:13,451 --> 00:02:15,752
Well, at least if he's busy

53
00:02:15,790 --> 00:02:19,629
he'll stop going on
about this wedding of his.

54
00:02:19,665 --> 00:02:21,829
Oh, there were times
aboard the <i>Rotarran</i>

55
00:02:21,870 --> 00:02:23,737
he nearly drove me mad.

56
00:02:23,774 --> 00:02:27,077
Until his son arrived,
it was all he could talk about.

57
00:02:27,114 --> 00:02:30,053
Then Alexander became
all he could talk about.

58
00:02:30,088 --> 00:02:33,687
The man is nothing
if not single-minded.

59
00:02:33,729 --> 00:02:35,562
I haven't met Worf's son yet.

60
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:37,593
What's he like?

61
00:02:37,638 --> 00:02:39,369
He's a fine boy...

62
00:02:39,408 --> 00:02:41,902
dedicated, eager.

63
00:02:41,947 --> 00:02:44,851
He has the heart of his father

64
00:02:44,887 --> 00:02:48,622
but he's not the best
soldier I've ever seen.

65
00:02:48,662 --> 00:02:51,327
But when he ordered me
to bring the system back on line

66
00:02:51,368 --> 00:02:52,860
I thought he was still talking

67
00:02:52,904 --> 00:02:54,874
about the hydro-static
system, so...

68
00:02:54,909 --> 00:02:56,242
You didn't engage the pumps

69
00:02:56,278 --> 00:02:57,975
while the check valves
were open.

70
00:02:58,016 --> 00:02:59,075
He did.

71
00:02:59,119 --> 00:03:01,055
I flooded the entire deck

72
00:03:01,089 --> 00:03:03,219
with super-heated
hydraulic fluid.

73
00:03:03,261 --> 00:03:05,163
It took me three days
to clean it up

74
00:03:05,198 --> 00:03:08,365
but, I swear, it still smells
like burnt dog hair in there.

75
00:03:08,439 --> 00:03:10,842
Remind me to keep you away
from the <i>Defiant.</i>

76
00:03:10,878 --> 00:03:11,846
You're a menace.

77
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:13,041
The <i>Rotarran's</i> crew

78
00:03:13,082 --> 00:03:15,553
actually thinks of me
as a good luck charm.

79
00:03:15,587 --> 00:03:19,892
You know, the more mistakes
I make, the safer they feel.

80
00:03:19,931 --> 00:03:22,732
I hope the <i>Ya'Vang's</i> crew
feels the same way.

81
00:03:22,770 --> 00:03:24,205
The <i>Ya'Vang?</i>

82
00:03:25,242 --> 00:03:27,041
I got new orders this morning.

83
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:29,847
The battle cruiser <i>Ya'Vang</i>
took heavy losses

84
00:03:29,886 --> 00:03:31,378
in their last engagement

85
00:03:31,422 --> 00:03:34,884
so most of the <i>Rotarran's</i> crew
are being transferred there

86
00:03:34,931 --> 00:03:37,129
at the end of the week,
including me.

87
00:03:39,273 --> 00:03:41,767
Uh, more bloodwine?

88
00:03:41,812 --> 00:03:42,939
Why not?

89
00:03:42,981 --> 00:03:44,883
No. Not for me.

90
00:03:46,990 --> 00:03:48,219
Handsome young man.

91
00:03:48,260 --> 00:03:50,788
He must get his looks
from his mother's side.

92
00:03:50,832 --> 00:03:52,324
What do you want?

93
00:03:52,369 --> 00:03:55,809
Have you had a chance
to reconsider my offer?

94
00:03:55,843 --> 00:03:58,076
We are not getting
married in this bar.

95
00:03:58,114 --> 00:04:01,281
The ceremony will take place
on the Klingon homeworld

96
00:04:01,321 --> 00:04:03,223
after the war.

97
00:04:03,260 --> 00:04:05,788
Worf, let's do it here,
this week

98
00:04:05,832 --> 00:04:07,267
before Alexander leaves.

99
00:04:07,301 --> 00:04:08,394
Perfect.

100
00:04:08,437 --> 00:04:09,838
I'll handle
all the arrangements.

101
00:04:09,873 --> 00:04:12,572
Wait. I thought
we had agreed.

102
00:04:12,613 --> 00:04:14,549
We did, but I would hate
for Alexander

103
00:04:14,584 --> 00:04:16,053
to miss his father's wedding.

104
00:04:16,087 --> 00:04:19,390
It would mean so much to him

105
00:04:19,428 --> 00:04:22,401
and besides,
it may be a long time

106
00:04:22,435 --> 00:04:25,408
before you see him again.

107
00:04:30,452 --> 00:04:32,753
What's going on?

108
00:04:35,764 --> 00:04:37,757
Our wedding plans have changed.

109
00:04:37,802 --> 00:04:41,105
We are getting married here
on Deep Space 9

110
00:04:41,142 --> 00:04:45,413
and I would like you
to be my <i>Tawi'Yan.</i>

111
00:04:47,624 --> 00:04:49,150
"Sword-bearer."

112
00:04:49,194 --> 00:04:52,167
It's sort of like a best man.

113
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:54,170
Me?

114
00:04:54,205 --> 00:04:55,538
Really?

115
00:04:55,641 --> 00:04:56,631
Oh, that's great!

116
00:05:00,652 --> 00:05:03,180
I'll put that on your tab.

117
00:07:02,648 --> 00:07:05,211
It doesn't leave much time
to make all the arrangements

118
00:07:05,254 --> 00:07:07,555
but fortunately, there isn't
that much left to do.

119
00:07:07,591 --> 00:07:09,652
Worf's been planning
the ceremony

120
00:07:09,696 --> 00:07:11,165
for the last three months.

121
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,863
He has everything figured out

122
00:07:12,903 --> 00:07:15,067
right down to the color
of my shoes.

123
00:07:15,109 --> 00:07:18,082
No offense, Jadzia,
but it seems like this wedding's

124
00:07:18,115 --> 00:07:19,584
all about what Worf wants.

125
00:07:19,652 --> 00:07:22,419
Uh, Habitat Ring,
Section 51 Gamma.

126
00:07:22,457 --> 00:07:23,550
What about you?

127
00:07:24,963 --> 00:07:27,127
A traditional Klingon wedding
with all the trimmings

128
00:07:27,168 --> 00:07:28,797
is something Worf's
been thinking about

129
00:07:28,838 --> 00:07:30,137
since he was a boy.

130
00:07:30,175 --> 00:07:32,738
It probably has something
to do with being raised

131
00:07:32,781 --> 00:07:34,273
by human parents.

132
00:07:34,318 --> 00:07:36,551
In any case, when it comes
to Klingon tradition

133
00:07:36,588 --> 00:07:37,749
Worf is very sentimental.

134
00:07:37,792 --> 00:07:39,261
Worf?

135
00:07:39,294 --> 00:07:41,424
All men are sentimental.

136
00:07:41,466 --> 00:07:44,928
They just cover it up with
scowls and clenched jaws.

137
00:07:44,973 --> 00:07:49,848
There are times when Worf
literally gets misty-eyed

138
00:07:49,884 --> 00:07:51,820
talking about Klingon rituals.

139
00:07:53,192 --> 00:07:55,162
So, uh, that's
why you're letting him

140
00:07:55,197 --> 00:07:56,860
make the plans for the wedding?

141
00:07:56,900 --> 00:07:58,836
Mostly, but the truth is

142
00:07:58,871 --> 00:08:01,206
I've already been through
five Trill ceremonies...

143
00:08:01,243 --> 00:08:03,110
three as a bride,
two as a groom,

144
00:08:03,147 --> 00:08:04,308
and I'm a little bored with it.

145
00:08:04,350 --> 00:08:05,511
Is it my imagination

146
00:08:05,552 --> 00:08:07,522
or did Odo just
try and avoid us?

147
00:08:07,556 --> 00:08:08,649
I didn't notice.

148
00:08:10,830 --> 00:08:12,299
We've been avoiding each other

149
00:08:12,334 --> 00:08:14,430
ever since the Dominion
left the station.

150
00:08:14,472 --> 00:08:16,135
I think we're both
afraid of talking

151
00:08:16,176 --> 00:08:18,146
about what happened
during the occupation.

152
00:08:18,180 --> 00:08:20,515
What do you mean?

153
00:08:20,552 --> 00:08:22,887
Oh, to tell you the truth

154
00:08:22,924 --> 00:08:26,295
it's nothing I want to talk
about right now either.

155
00:08:29,271 --> 00:08:30,638
Thank you for coming.

156
00:08:30,674 --> 00:08:32,200
As you probably know by now

157
00:08:32,244 --> 00:08:35,403
Jadzia and I will be married
here on the station in six days.

158
00:08:35,536 --> 00:08:36,971
There's nothing more romantic

159
00:08:37,006 --> 00:08:39,239
than a wedding
on DS9 in springtime.

160
00:08:39,277 --> 00:08:41,110
When the neutrinos are in bloom.

161
00:08:41,149 --> 00:08:43,620
By tradition,
the Klingon man spends

162
00:08:43,654 --> 00:08:45,647
the four nights
before his wedding

163
00:08:45,692 --> 00:08:47,925
on a mental
and spiritual journey.

164
00:08:47,964 --> 00:08:51,369
It is called <i>Kal'Hyah,</i>
"The Path of Clarity"

165
00:08:51,404 --> 00:08:55,470
and he is accompanied
by his closest male friends.

166
00:08:55,514 --> 00:08:58,042
You cannot imagine
the experience that awaits us...

167
00:08:58,086 --> 00:09:02,619
four long nights filled
with song and fellowship.

168
00:09:02,662 --> 00:09:04,997
A time of unbridled pleasures.

169
00:09:05,034 --> 00:09:08,633
Are we talking
about a bachelor party here?

170
00:09:08,676 --> 00:09:10,339
It is a similar ritual.

171
00:09:10,446 --> 00:09:11,539
Sounds good to me.

172
00:09:11,582 --> 00:09:12,572
Me, too.

173
00:09:13,587 --> 00:09:15,318
Count me in.

174
00:09:15,357 --> 00:09:18,592
We will meet in the holosuite
tomorrow night at 2100 hours.

175
00:09:18,631 --> 00:09:20,795
I advise you all
to get plenty of rest.

176
00:09:20,835 --> 00:09:23,068
Four nights
at a Klingon bachelor party.

177
00:09:23,107 --> 00:09:24,974
Just think of the possibilities.

178
00:09:25,011 --> 00:09:26,537
Thank God Keiko's not here.

179
00:09:26,582 --> 00:09:28,313
I wonder what Dax will be doing

180
00:09:28,352 --> 00:09:30,345
while we're traveling
down <i>Kal'Hyah.</i>

181
00:09:30,390 --> 00:09:32,725
She will be taking
a different journey...

182
00:09:32,761 --> 00:09:35,665
with my wife.

183
00:09:35,702 --> 00:09:38,037
Your wife?

184
00:09:42,116 --> 00:09:43,243
By marrying Worf

185
00:09:43,285 --> 00:09:45,415
Dax will be joining
the House of Martok.

186
00:09:45,457 --> 00:09:47,427
Since the mistress
of a great House

187
00:09:47,494 --> 00:09:48,986
must approve all marriages

188
00:09:49,031 --> 00:09:51,058
Sirella will spend
the next four days

189
00:09:51,102 --> 00:09:52,401
evaluating Jadzia.

190
00:10:00,490 --> 00:10:02,289
My lady.

191
00:10:02,327 --> 00:10:05,026
You've put on weight...

192
00:10:05,066 --> 00:10:07,435
and your hair is going gray.

193
00:10:08,473 --> 00:10:13,576
My deterioration
is proceeding apace.

194
00:10:13,618 --> 00:10:16,648
I thought you would be
in your grave by now.

195
00:10:17,727 --> 00:10:19,458
I shall endeavor to die...

196
00:10:19,498 --> 00:10:21,331
this year, if possible.

197
00:10:21,369 --> 00:10:24,205
Allow me to present
Captain Benjamin Sisko

198
00:10:24,241 --> 00:10:26,177
Commander of Deep Space 9.

199
00:10:26,213 --> 00:10:28,446
Captain, may I present

200
00:10:28,484 --> 00:10:31,354
the mistress of the House
of Martok, my wife

201
00:10:31,391 --> 00:10:33,293
and the mother of my children...

202
00:10:33,328 --> 00:10:35,799
Sirella, daughter of Linkasa.

203
00:10:35,834 --> 00:10:37,531
Welcome to Deep Space 9.

204
00:10:38,573 --> 00:10:40,669
Thank you, Captain.

205
00:10:40,711 --> 00:10:42,203
Where is she?

206
00:10:42,248 --> 00:10:44,719
Jadzia's quarters are
in the Habitat Ring

207
00:10:44,754 --> 00:10:47,385
Section... 25 Alpha.

208
00:10:47,426 --> 00:10:48,793
Shall I escort you?

209
00:10:48,829 --> 00:10:50,560
It's quite far away.

210
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,035
I'll find my way.

211
00:10:55,544 --> 00:10:57,879
If you'll excuse me.

212
00:11:00,053 --> 00:11:03,686
Magnificent, isn't she?

213
00:11:12,614 --> 00:11:15,518
Are those real <i>var'Hama</i> candles?

214
00:11:15,555 --> 00:11:17,719
Yes, Worf, I traveled to Kronos.

215
00:11:17,759 --> 00:11:20,755
I captured three <i>targs</i>
in the Hamar mountains

216
00:11:20,799 --> 00:11:22,769
made the ritual sacrifice
at dawn

217
00:11:22,803 --> 00:11:24,397
came back to the station

218
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:27,777
asked Quark to boil
their shoulders into tallow.

219
00:11:27,814 --> 00:11:30,513
Then, I spent two days
molding them into candles

220
00:11:30,554 --> 00:11:31,579
with my own hands.

221
00:11:31,656 --> 00:11:33,889
I was just asking.

222
00:11:33,928 --> 00:11:37,026
You were criticizing again.

223
00:11:37,068 --> 00:11:39,767
Relax.
She's not going to reject

224
00:11:39,808 --> 00:11:40,901
a prospective daughter

225
00:11:40,943 --> 00:11:42,344
because the <i>var'Hama</i> candles

226
00:11:42,380 --> 00:11:44,213
in her welcoming
display were replicated.

227
00:11:45,253 --> 00:11:46,243
Come in.

228
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:55,001
<i>Tug son bosh mok</i>
<i>A 'Beh, Sirella koH.</i>

229
00:11:55,041 --> 00:11:57,911
<i>E'Gagh vet moh.</i>

230
00:11:57,948 --> 00:12:00,283
What is he doing here?

231
00:12:00,319 --> 00:12:01,845
I meant no disrespect.

232
00:12:01,889 --> 00:12:03,222
Then leave.

233
00:12:11,477 --> 00:12:15,316
Your worthiness to join
our House will now be judged

234
00:12:15,352 --> 00:12:18,325
according to the traditions
of my family.

235
00:12:18,359 --> 00:12:19,726
I am prepared, my lady.

236
00:12:19,762 --> 00:12:21,197
I doubt that.

237
00:12:21,231 --> 00:12:25,639
A Klingon woman would find it
difficult to gain my favor.

238
00:12:25,709 --> 00:12:28,237
For... an alien

239
00:12:28,281 --> 00:12:30,752
it will most likely
be impossible.

240
00:12:30,786 --> 00:12:32,779
I like a challenge.

241
00:12:32,824 --> 00:12:36,765
I will not have my authority
challenged by you.

242
00:12:36,799 --> 00:12:39,236
That's not what I meant.

243
00:12:39,271 --> 00:12:42,301
If you cannot say what you mean,
say nothing at all.

244
00:12:43,481 --> 00:12:46,818
The evaluation
will begin tomorrow morning.

245
00:12:46,855 --> 00:12:50,192
Have the traditional meal
prepared before I arrive.

246
00:12:51,832 --> 00:12:53,495
And in the future

247
00:12:53,536 --> 00:12:58,309
if you cannot trouble yourself
to make real <i>var'Hama</i> candles

248
00:12:58,347 --> 00:13:01,183
try not to use
such obvious fakes.

249
00:13:17,088 --> 00:13:20,357
You never told me that your wife
was opposed to this marriage.

250
00:13:20,395 --> 00:13:22,525
Sirella is a woman
of strong convictions.

251
00:13:22,567 --> 00:13:24,434
She believes
that by bringing aliens

252
00:13:24,471 --> 00:13:26,908
into our families,
we risk losing our identity

253
00:13:26,943 --> 00:13:28,002
as Klingons.

254
00:13:28,045 --> 00:13:30,209
That is a prejudiced,
xenophobic view.

255
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:31,810
We are Klingons, Worf.

256
00:13:31,854 --> 00:13:34,155
We don't embrace other cultures.

257
00:13:34,192 --> 00:13:35,353
We conquer them.

258
00:13:35,394 --> 00:13:36,886
If someone wishes

259
00:13:36,931 --> 00:13:39,562
to join us,
they must honor our traditions

260
00:13:39,604 --> 00:13:41,301
and prove themselves worthy

261
00:13:41,341 --> 00:13:43,744
of wearing the crest
of a Great House.

262
00:13:43,779 --> 00:13:45,214
Jadzia is worthy.

263
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:47,015
Of course she is.

264
00:13:47,053 --> 00:13:50,288
She's an honorable woman
and a formidable warrior.

265
00:13:50,327 --> 00:13:52,263
You should say that to Sirella.

266
00:13:53,268 --> 00:13:55,466
That's not such a good idea.

267
00:13:55,505 --> 00:13:57,669
I don't want her to think

268
00:13:57,710 --> 00:14:01,115
that I'm interfering
in her domain.

269
00:14:02,153 --> 00:14:04,123
Perhaps I should speak with her.

270
00:14:04,158 --> 00:14:07,256
Coming from me, it would
not seem like a challenge

271
00:14:07,299 --> 00:14:08,267
to her authority.

272
00:14:08,301 --> 00:14:09,770
I wouldn't do that
if I were you.

273
00:14:12,343 --> 00:14:13,368
Why?

274
00:14:14,414 --> 00:14:16,247
Well, um...

275
00:14:16,284 --> 00:14:18,983
the truth is...

276
00:14:19,024 --> 00:14:21,461
she doesn't like you
that much either.

277
00:14:21,496 --> 00:14:22,464
Me.

278
00:14:22,498 --> 00:14:25,197
Don't let that bother you.

279
00:14:25,238 --> 00:14:28,211
I had every right
to bring you into the family

280
00:14:28,245 --> 00:14:30,010
and she's accepted the fact

281
00:14:30,048 --> 00:14:32,679
that there's nothing
she can do about it.

282
00:14:32,721 --> 00:14:34,156
How comforting.

283
00:14:39,669 --> 00:14:43,701
And they say that you
have no sense of humor.

284
00:15:00,716 --> 00:15:03,017
Phew. I could do
without the heat.

285
00:15:03,054 --> 00:15:06,118
I can't, uh, say much
for the decor either.

286
00:15:06,161 --> 00:15:08,598
Well, it can't be
all fun and games.

287
00:15:08,633 --> 00:15:11,629
I'm sure there has to be
some sort of ritual

288
00:15:11,673 --> 00:15:14,805
we have to go through
before the party begins.

289
00:15:14,847 --> 00:15:17,717
There is going to be
a party, isn't there?

290
00:15:17,753 --> 00:15:19,188
You're asking me?

291
00:15:19,223 --> 00:15:22,219
I can barely say
my name in Klingon.

292
00:15:22,262 --> 00:15:24,995
Prepare yourselves, my friends

293
00:15:25,036 --> 00:15:27,769
for a journey
you won't soon forget.

294
00:15:33,454 --> 00:15:34,980
These...

295
00:15:35,024 --> 00:15:36,425
are <i>Ma'Stakas.</i>

296
00:15:36,460 --> 00:15:38,362
What, uh, what do
we do with them?

297
00:15:38,399 --> 00:15:40,734
At the conclusion
of the wedding ceremony

298
00:15:40,771 --> 00:15:43,106
you will use them
to attack Worf and Dax.

299
00:15:43,142 --> 00:15:45,009
Obviously.
Don't you know anything?

300
00:15:45,046 --> 00:15:46,070
The tradition dates back

301
00:15:46,203 --> 00:15:47,797
to the wedding
of Kahless and Lukara

302
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:49,810
who were nearly killed
by Molor's troops

303
00:15:49,844 --> 00:15:51,438
moments after they were married.

304
00:15:51,481 --> 00:15:52,540
Until the ceremony,

305
00:15:52,584 --> 00:15:54,714
you should keep these with you
at all times.

306
00:15:54,755 --> 00:15:58,388
I trust
this combat is non-lethal.

307
00:15:58,430 --> 00:16:01,061
It is a symbolic attack only.

308
00:16:01,103 --> 00:16:02,298
Oh.

309
00:16:03,775 --> 00:16:06,771
That food is not to be eaten.

310
00:16:08,286 --> 00:16:09,721
Then what is it for?

311
00:16:09,755 --> 00:16:12,922
It is there to tempt us
to break our fast.

312
00:16:12,962 --> 00:16:14,089
Fast?

313
00:16:14,132 --> 00:16:15,692
There are six trials

314
00:16:15,734 --> 00:16:17,967
