all right.

325
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:40,784
How would you know?

326
00:16:40,824 --> 00:16:42,954
It is time to begin.

327
00:16:48,006 --> 00:16:50,136
Need more flowers
on the banister.

328
00:16:50,177 --> 00:16:51,874
We're ready with the banner,
boss.

329
00:16:53,117 --> 00:16:54,210
Raise it.

330
00:16:54,253 --> 00:16:55,882
You're up early.

331
00:16:55,923 --> 00:16:57,358
I thought writers slept late.

332
00:16:57,393 --> 00:16:58,361
Not always.

333
00:16:58,396 --> 00:17:00,332
I sold my first book today.

334
00:17:00,366 --> 00:17:03,464
Really?
How much did you get for it?

335
00:17:03,507 --> 00:17:05,409
It's just a figure of speech.

336
00:17:05,444 --> 00:17:06,503
The Federation News Service

337
00:17:06,546 --> 00:17:08,106
is going to publish
a book of my stories

338
00:17:08,150 --> 00:17:09,983
about life on the station
under Dominion rule.

339
00:17:10,021 --> 00:17:11,046
And they're not paying you?

340
00:17:11,090 --> 00:17:12,149
No.

341
00:17:12,192 --> 00:17:14,162
Well, then you have
my sympathies

342
00:17:14,197 --> 00:17:16,030
and the first round
of drinks is on the house.

343
00:17:16,068 --> 00:17:17,161
Really?

344
00:17:17,203 --> 00:17:20,404
No. It's a figure of speech.

345
00:17:20,444 --> 00:17:22,505
Look, I want to tell
my dad about the book.

346
00:17:22,549 --> 00:17:23,710
Is he still in the holosuite?

347
00:17:23,751 --> 00:17:26,416
Oh, yeah.
They're still up there.

348
00:17:26,457 --> 00:17:28,393
What are they doing?

349
00:17:28,428 --> 00:17:31,025
It's a Klingon bachelor party.

350
