486
00:24:44,665 --> 00:24:49,198
Lieutenant Manuele Atoa
from the Starship <i>Sutherland.</i>

487
00:24:49,242 --> 00:24:51,338
I've never seen
anything like that.

488
00:24:51,380 --> 00:24:52,507
Neither have I.

489
00:24:55,957 --> 00:24:57,517
Let's get something to eat.

490
00:24:59,464 --> 00:25:01,366
A woman of many talents.

491
00:25:01,402 --> 00:25:04,807
It's a shame she's
about to waste them all

492
00:25:04,843 --> 00:25:07,679
on that walking frown
she calls a fiancé.

493
00:25:07,716 --> 00:25:09,049
She's too good for him.

494
00:25:09,086 --> 00:25:10,419
I've said that
from the beginning.

495
00:25:10,455 --> 00:25:11,616
Are you jealous?

496
00:25:13,128 --> 00:25:14,859
There's no profit in jealousy.

497
00:25:14,899 --> 00:25:17,268
That's not a denial.

498
00:25:20,277 --> 00:25:22,304
It's not to be quoted either.

499
00:25:22,348 --> 00:25:23,373
Oh, don't worry.

500
00:25:23,417 --> 00:25:24,784
So when did you first realize

501
00:25:24,820 --> 00:25:26,346
