but they worked it out.

524
00:26:44,495 --> 00:26:46,488
How long will this...

525
00:26:46,533 --> 00:26:48,196
party continue?

526
00:26:48,237 --> 00:26:52,235
This party will continue
until further notice

527
00:26:52,278 --> 00:26:56,276
on the personal authority
of this station's First Officer

528
00:26:56,321 --> 00:26:57,620
who just happens to be me.

529
00:26:57,657 --> 00:26:58,716
Mm-hmm.

530
00:26:58,759 --> 00:27:00,558
You're in a good mood.

531
00:27:00,597 --> 00:27:02,932
Well, it's a good party.

532
00:27:03,971 --> 00:27:05,463
Well...

533
00:27:05,508 --> 00:27:06,533
Odo...

534
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:09,679
Odo...

535
00:27:09,717 --> 00:27:12,781
I think we have
a lot to talk about.

536
00:27:13,926 --> 00:27:14,894
I agree.

537
00:27:14,929 --> 00:27:16,626
So let's talk.

538
00:27:16,666 --> 00:27:18,533
Now?

539
00:27:18,570 --> 00:27:20,700
Don't you think we've
put it off long enough?

540
00:27:22,879 --> 00:27:24,872
Enjoy yourselves.

541
00:27:26,420 --> 00:27:28,151
Let's, um...

542
00:27:28,191 --> 00:27:30,252
find someplace a little quieter.

543
00:27:39,749 --> 00:27:41,742
Thanks for the show.

544
00:27:41,788 --> 00:27:43,781
Thanks for getting me
the day off.

545
00:27:43,825 --> 00:27:45,624
Captain Shelby owed me a favor.

546
00:27:45,662 --> 00:27:47,256
Actually, owed me several.

547
00:27:47,299 --> 00:27:49,702
In fact, how would
you like to have

548
00:27:49,738 --> 00:27:51,605
another two days off?

549
00:27:51,643 --> 00:27:53,112
Two?

550
00:27:53,179 --> 00:27:54,648
What do I have to do?

551
00:27:54,682 --> 00:27:55,650
Not much.

552
00:27:55,684 --> 00:27:57,620
Just give me something
fun to look at

553
00:27:57,656 --> 00:27:59,489
for the rest of the evening.

554
00:27:59,526 --> 00:28:00,494
Anything else?

555
00:28:00,528 --> 00:28:02,521
I'll let you know.

556
00:28:02,567 --> 00:28:04,161
You!

557
00:28:05,673 --> 00:28:08,042
Leave her
or I'll cut your head off

558
00:28:08,078 --> 00:28:09,843
and hang it from my belt.

559
00:28:09,882 --> 00:28:11,647
I'll take care of this.

560
00:28:13,658 --> 00:28:15,287
You weren't invited.

561
00:28:15,328 --> 00:28:18,095
It is time
for the <i>Bre'Nan</i> ritual.

562
00:28:18,134 --> 00:28:19,797
I'm busy.

563
00:28:19,837 --> 00:28:23,538
Busy acting like a Risian slut.

564
00:28:24,548 --> 00:28:26,985
I'm only going to ask
you to leave once.

565
00:28:27,020 --> 00:28:29,423
You will come
with me now and perform

566
00:28:29,459 --> 00:28:31,896
the Bre'Nan ritual
to my satisfaction

567
00:28:31,931 --> 00:28:33,958
or I will cancel your wedding.

568
00:28:34,002 --> 00:28:35,403
<i>Toruk-DOH!</i>

569
00:28:37,911 --> 00:28:39,312
Ladies, please.

570
00:28:39,348 --> 00:28:42,844
<i>Mok'Ta vor kash a'VEH!</i>

571
00:28:49,870 --> 00:28:52,000
Why is everyone standing around?

572
00:28:52,042 --> 00:28:54,172
The party's
just getting started.

573
00:28:54,214 --> 00:28:55,513
Play something!

574
00:29:14,056 --> 00:29:16,357
Double <i>raktajino,</i> extra sweet.

575
00:29:20,371 --> 00:29:22,899
What time is it?

576
00:29:22,943 --> 00:29:24,469
1030 hours.

577
00:29:25,715 --> 00:29:26,842
Come on.

578
00:29:30,626 --> 00:29:32,687
Wrong door.

579
00:29:39,078 --> 00:29:41,048
Excuse me, sir.

580
00:29:49,568 --> 00:29:50,693
Jadzia, we need to...

581
00:29:50,693 --> 00:29:52,356
Jadzia, we need to...

582
00:29:55,537 --> 00:29:57,507
You're mad.

583
00:29:57,541 --> 00:29:59,808
I am concerned.

584
00:29:59,846 --> 00:30:01,839
Yeah, well, I'm hung over.

585
00:30:01,951 --> 00:30:03,386
Can we talk later?

586
00:30:03,421 --> 00:30:05,790
We have a very serious problem.

587
00:30:05,826 --> 00:30:08,491
Sirella has canceled
the wedding.

588
00:30:08,533 --> 00:30:11,403
She doesn't waste
any time, does she?

589
00:30:11,438 --> 00:30:13,568
She said you attacked her.

590
00:30:15,581 --> 00:30:17,210
She pulled a knife.

591
00:30:22,029 --> 00:30:24,865
You are forbidden to join
the House of Martok.

592
00:30:24,901 --> 00:30:27,840
So I won't be invited
to the family picnics.

593
00:30:27,875 --> 00:30:29,538
I'll live.

594
00:30:29,579 --> 00:30:31,014
I cannot believe
how you're taking

595
00:30:31,049 --> 00:30:32,039
this so lightly.

596
00:30:32,084 --> 00:30:33,576
Do you hear that?

597
00:30:33,621 --> 00:30:35,090
What?

598
00:30:36,627 --> 00:30:38,757
It sounds like voices.

599
00:30:43,476 --> 00:30:45,674
- Hi.
- Hi.

600
00:30:45,714 --> 00:30:47,844
Is the party over?

601
00:30:47,886 --> 00:30:49,947
You could say that.

602
00:30:50,023 --> 00:30:51,116
It's 10:30.

603
00:30:51,159 --> 00:30:52,594
In the morning?

604
00:30:52,629 --> 00:30:53,790
I'm on duty.

605
00:30:53,832 --> 00:30:55,301
So am I.

606
00:30:55,335 --> 00:30:56,634
It was a great party.

607
00:30:56,671 --> 00:30:58,072
Thanks.

608
00:31:05,190 --> 00:31:07,217
We must deal
with the situation now.

609
00:31:07,261 --> 00:31:08,422
Stop yelling.

610
00:31:08,463 --> 00:31:09,692
My head hurts.

611
00:31:10,936 --> 00:31:13,932
You must go to Sirella
and beg her forgiveness.

612
00:31:21,426 --> 00:31:22,952
I don't beg.

613
00:31:23,029 --> 00:31:26,696
You are allowing
your pride to blind you.

614
00:31:26,737 --> 00:31:27,705
Look who's talking.

615
00:31:27,740 --> 00:31:29,801
You want me to go crawling
to some old hag

616
00:31:29,844 --> 00:31:32,543
just so you can have your
traditional Klingon wedding.

617
00:31:32,583 --> 00:31:35,111
This is about more
than just tradition.

618
00:31:37,527 --> 00:31:40,864
You and I have embarked
on a spiritual journey

619
00:31:40,901 --> 00:31:42,495
one that will bind us together

620
00:31:42,538 --> 00:31:44,839
through this life
and into the next.

621
00:31:44,877 --> 00:31:46,278
You cannot turn back now.

622
00:31:46,314 --> 00:31:48,979
Maybe you're on a
spiritual journey, Worf

623
00:31:49,020 --> 00:31:51,013
but I just want to get married.

624
00:31:51,058 --> 00:31:54,759
So why don't you go back
to sweating and bleeding

625
00:31:54,799 --> 00:31:56,530
with your friends
in the holosuite

626
00:31:56,569 --> 00:31:57,902
and when you're done

627
00:31:57,939 --> 00:31:59,738
meet me in Benjamin's office

628
00:31:59,777 --> 00:32:01,144
and he'll perform the ceremony.

629
00:32:09,665 --> 00:32:14,004
If that is your attitude...

630
00:32:14,075 --> 00:32:16,945
perhaps Sirella
was right about you.

631
00:32:19,587 --> 00:32:21,956
There should be no wedding.

632
00:32:23,261 --> 00:32:25,163
That's fine with me.

633
00:32:48,150 --> 00:32:49,676
What's going on?

634
00:32:49,720 --> 00:32:50,745
Haven't you heard?

635
00:32:50,788 --> 00:32:51,813
The wedding's off.

636
00:32:51,857 --> 00:32:53,588
Off? Why?

637
00:32:53,629 --> 00:32:57,764
She says it's because he's
a pig-headed, stubborn man

638
00:32:57,804 --> 00:33:00,800
who puts tradition
before everything else.

639
00:33:00,844 --> 00:33:03,543
He says it's because
she's a frivolous

640
00:33:03,583 --> 00:33:04,847
emotional woman

641
00:33:04,886 --> 00:33:07,585
who refuses to take him
or his culture seriously.

642
00:33:07,625 --> 00:33:09,618
You can see the problem.

643
00:33:09,664 --> 00:33:11,361
They're both right.

644
00:33:11,401 --> 00:33:12,562
Exactly.

645
00:33:12,603 --> 00:33:15,770
Well... there's only
one thing for it.

646
00:33:17,214 --> 00:33:19,549
Dinner.

647
00:33:19,586 --> 00:33:21,283
I'll get the menu.

648
00:33:31,478 --> 00:33:32,811
Enter.

649
00:33:39,830 --> 00:33:41,800
Worf...

650
00:33:41,834 --> 00:33:44,203
you've made a grave error.

651
00:33:46,344 --> 00:33:49,145
Perhaps.

652
00:33:49,217 --> 00:33:51,450
Do you still love her?

653
00:33:51,489 --> 00:33:53,550
Of course.

654
00:33:53,593 --> 00:33:56,794
However, in this case, that...

655
00:33:56,833 --> 00:33:58,427
may not be enough.

656
00:34:00,742 --> 00:34:03,738
Anyone can see that we are
hopelessly mismatched.

657
00:34:03,783 --> 00:34:06,084
She is a Trill;
I am a Klingon.

658
00:34:06,120 --> 00:34:08,921
She has had five marriages.

659
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:11,124
This would be my first.

660
00:34:11,198 --> 00:34:13,999
When she is laughing,
I am somber.

661
00:34:14,038 --> 00:34:16,134
When I am happy, she is crying.

662
00:34:16,176 --> 00:34:19,149
She plays <i>tongo</i> with
the Ferengi bartender.

663
00:34:19,249 --> 00:34:21,720
I can barely stand him.

664
00:34:23,659 --> 00:34:26,598
She mocks everything...

665
00:34:26,632 --> 00:34:29,399
while I take
everything seriously.

666
00:34:32,178 --> 00:34:37,019
She is nothing like the woman
I thought I would marry.

667
00:34:37,055 --> 00:34:39,356
We are not accorded
the luxury

668
00:34:39,394 --> 00:34:42,834
of choosing the women
we fall in love with.

669
00:34:42,868 --> 00:34:46,000
Do you think Sirella
is anything like the woman

670
00:34:46,041 --> 00:34:49,503
I thought that I'd marry?

671
00:34:49,549 --> 00:34:54,322
She is a prideful,
arrogant, mercurial woman

672
00:34:54,360 --> 00:35:00,671
who shares my bed far too
infrequently for my taste.

673
00:35:00,707 --> 00:35:04,169
And yet...

674
00:35:04,215 --> 00:35:06,618
I love her...

675
00:35:06,654 --> 00:35:08,647
deeply.

676
00:35:08,691 --> 00:35:10,422
Hmm.

677
00:35:10,463 --> 00:35:14,962
We Klingons often tout our...

678
00:35:15,005 --> 00:35:17,442
prowess in battle...

679
00:35:17,478 --> 00:35:21,442
our desire for glory and honor
above all else...

680
00:35:23,257 --> 00:35:27,028
but how hollow is
the sound of victory...

681
00:35:27,065 --> 00:35:28,830
without someone
to share it with?

682
00:35:28,870 --> 00:35:32,207
Honor gives little comfort

683
00:35:32,244 --> 00:35:34,841
to a man alone in his home...

684
00:35:34,883 --> 00:35:37,081
and in his heart.

685
00:35:43,301 --> 00:35:44,600
One steak with mushrooms

686
00:35:44,637 --> 00:35:46,539
baked potato, sour cream
and chives.

687
00:35:46,575 --> 00:35:47,839
I should have had that.

688
00:35:47,877 --> 00:35:50,873
One double Altair sandwich,
no mustard...

689
00:35:50,918 --> 00:35:52,820
two bowls of linguini

690
00:35:52,855 --> 00:35:56,090
Bajoran shrimp
with extra cheese.

691
00:35:56,129 --> 00:35:59,159
One loaf of mapa bread.

692
00:35:59,202 --> 00:36:00,694
Quark, where's the <i>kava</i> juice?

693
00:36:00,739 --> 00:36:02,106
They're still
squeezing the roots

694
00:36:02,142 --> 00:36:03,577
unless you want replicated.

695
00:36:03,612 --> 00:36:04,979
We'll wait.

696
00:36:05,015 --> 00:36:07,042
What do you think you're doing?

697
00:36:08,423 --> 00:36:09,618
The wedding's been called off.

698
00:36:09,658 --> 00:36:10,683
It's back on.

699
00:36:10,728 --> 00:36:13,359
Worf is apologizing
to Jadzia

700
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:14,664
at this very moment.

701
00:36:14,704 --> 00:36:16,173
Quark, take it all away.

702
00:36:16,206 --> 00:36:18,507
No food for those
on the path to <i>Kal'Hyah.</i>

703
00:36:18,545 --> 00:36:22,246
No refunds for those
on the path to <i>Kal'Hyah</i> as well.

704
00:36:22,287 --> 00:36:23,654
Sorry.

705
00:36:28,266 --> 00:36:30,499
Father, what happened?

706
00:36:32,909 --> 00:36:34,845
She refused to change her mind

707
00:36:34,881 --> 00:36:37,079
and the wedding is still off.

708
00:36:38,389 --> 00:36:39,482
Where is she?

709
00:36:39,524 --> 00:36:41,517
In her quarters.

710
00:36:41,562 --> 00:36:43,658
I'll go talk to her.

711
00:36:43,700 --> 00:36:46,696
Just... keep them away
from the food?

712
00:36:54,691 --> 00:36:56,160
Come in!

713
00:36:57,931 --> 00:36:59,332
Save your breath.

714
00:36:59,368 --> 00:37:01,839
Worf's gone too far,
and now it's over.

715
00:37:01,873 --> 00:37:03,412
Do you know
what he wanted me to do?

716
00:37:03,545 --> 00:37:06,985
He wanted me to go crawling
on my hands and knees to Sirella

717
00:37:07,019 --> 00:37:08,420
to beg her forgiveness.

718
00:37:08,456 --> 00:37:09,948
Beg her! Me!

719
00:37:09,993 --> 00:37:11,724
I was once

720
00:37:11,763 --> 00:37:14,827
the Federation Ambassador
to the Klingon Empire.

721
00:37:16,741 --> 00:37:19,042
I negotiated
the Khitomer Accords

722
00:37:19,080 --> 00:37:20,515
before Worf was even born.

723
00:37:20,549 --> 00:37:22,348
Curzon negotiated the Accords!

724
00:37:22,387 --> 00:37:24,357
And I've got news for you,
old man.

725
00:37:24,391 --> 00:37:25,917
You're not Curzon anymore.

726
00:37:25,961 --> 00:37:28,022
And what the hell is that
supposed to mean?

727
00:37:28,065 --> 00:37:30,058
It means that you
can't expect Sirella

728
00:37:30,104 --> 00:37:31,437
to treat you like Curzon

729
00:37:31,474 --> 00:37:33,501
just because you carry
his memories.

730
00:37:33,545 --> 00:37:35,447
To her, you're
just a young woman

731
00:37:35,482 --> 00:37:37,749
who decided to marry
into her family.

732
00:37:37,787 --> 00:37:40,817
If it means you have to bow down
and kiss her boots

733
00:37:40,894 --> 00:37:44,197
that's exactly what you have
to do, and you knew that.

734
00:37:44,235 --> 00:37:46,262
The moment you decided
to marry Worf

735
00:37:46,306 --> 00:37:49,210
you knew that sooner or later
you'd have to bow down

736
00:37:49,246 --> 00:37:51,547
and show her the respect
that she's due.

737
00:37:51,585 --> 00:37:53,214
This is Worf's fault...

738
00:37:53,255 --> 00:37:55,556
Worf and his traditional
Klingon wedding.

739
00:37:55,593 --> 00:37:58,326
Well, he may have let
this wedding business

740
00:37:58,366 --> 00:38:02,033
go to his head,
but you are 356 years old.

741
00:38:02,074 --> 00:38:04,807
Compared to you,
Worf is just a kid

742
00:38:04,847 --> 00:38:08,116
and if you can't abide
by Klingon traditions

743
00:38:08,153 --> 00:38:10,488
then you never should
have let yourself

744
00:38:10,525 --> 00:38:14,090
fall in love with him
in the first place.

745
00:38:14,134 --> 00:38:17,505
And you are in love with him.

746
00:38:19,947 --> 00:38:22,384
I wasn't looking
to fall in love.

747
00:38:22,419 --> 00:38:25,084
I was perfectly happy
by myself.

748
00:38:25,125 --> 00:38:28,656
I had friends, a career,
adventure...

749
00:38:31,438 --> 00:38:34,434
Then one day...

750
00:38:34,478 --> 00:38:39,649
this Klingon with a bad attitude
walked into my life

751
00:38:39,690 --> 00:38:43,756
and the next thing I know,
I'm getting married.

752
00:38:43,799 --> 00:38:49,141
After 356 years
and seven lifetimes...

753
00:38:49,178 --> 00:38:51,411
I still lead with my heart.

754
00:38:51,449 --> 00:38:53,078
You know, that is

755
00:38:53,119 --> 00:38:55,682
what I've always loved
about you.

756
00:38:58,398 --> 00:39:01,165
And I think that's why
Worf loves you, too.

757
00:39:10,491 --> 00:39:13,760
Whatever happened
to that young, callow Ensign

758
00:39:13,798 --> 00:39:16,429
I used to know?

759
00:39:16,470 --> 00:39:21,915
The one who used to turn to me
for advice all the time?

760
00:39:21,983 --> 00:39:26,118
You know, the one with hair?

761
00:39:26,159 --> 00:39:28,152
I grew up.

762
00:39:31,805 --> 00:39:35,245
I guess it's time
I grow up, too.

763
00:39:35,279 --> 00:39:37,272
Mmm.

764
00:40:17,639 --> 00:40:19,632
With fire and steel

765
00:40:19,676 --> 00:40:23,275
did the gods forge
the Klingon heart.

766
00:40:23,317 --> 00:40:25,344
So fiercely did it beat

767
00:40:25,389 --> 00:40:29,387
so loud was the sound,
that the gods cried out

768
00:40:29,431 --> 00:40:31,959
"On this day
we have brought forth

769
00:40:32,003 --> 00:40:35,670
"the strongest heart
in all the heavens.

770
00:40:35,711 --> 00:40:39,584
"None can stand before it
without trembling

771
00:40:39,620 --> 00:40:41,853
at its strength."

772
00:40:41,892 --> 00:40:44,022
But then the Klingon heart
weakened

773
00:40:44,063 --> 00:40:46,694
its steady rhythm faltered
and the gods said

774
00:40:46,736 --> 00:40:48,729
"Why have you weakened so?

775
00:40:48,773 --> 00:40:53,773
"We have made you the strongest
in all of creation."

776
00:40:53,818 --> 00:40:55,685
And the heart said...

777
00:40:55,722 --> 00:40:58,786
I am alone.

778
00:40:58,829 --> 00:41:01,494
And the gods knew
that they had erred.

779
00:41:01,534 --> 00:41:03,903
So they went back to their forge

780
00:41:03,940 --> 00:41:06,468
and brought forth...
another heart.

781
00:41:35,476 --> 00:41:39,417
But the second heart
beat stronger than the first

782
00:41:39,452 --> 00:41:42,425
and the first was jealous
of its power.

783
00:41:46,968 --> 00:41:48,369
Fortunately...

784
00:41:48,404 --> 00:41:51,844
the second heart was tempered
by wisdom.

785
00:41:51,879 --> 00:41:56,082
If we join together,
no force can stop us.

786
00:42:03,003 --> 00:42:06,808
And when the two hearts
began to beat together

787
00:42:06,845 --> 00:42:10,684
they filled the heavens
with a terrible sound.

788
00:42:10,720 --> 00:42:14,353
For the first time,
the gods knew fear.

789
00:42:14,395 --> 00:42:17,891
They tried to flee,
but it was too late.

790
00:42:17,936 --> 00:42:21,137
The Klingon hearts
destroyed the gods

791
00:42:21,177 --> 00:42:22,167
who created them

792
00:42:22,245 --> 00:42:25,081
and turned the heavens
to ashes.

793
00:42:25,118 --> 00:42:27,054
To this very day

794
00:42:27,089 --> 00:42:32,226
no one can oppose the beating
of two Klingon hearts.

795
00:42:34,739 --> 00:42:37,643
Not even me.

796
00:42:40,919 --> 00:42:45,054
Worf, son of Mogh,
does your heart beat

797
00:42:45,095 --> 00:42:47,589
only for this woman?

798
00:42:47,634 --> 00:42:48,829
Yes.

799
00:42:48,870 --> 00:42:52,332
And will you swear
to join with her

800
00:42:52,378 --> 00:42:55,715
and stand with her
against all who oppose you?

801
00:42:55,752 --> 00:42:58,383
I swear.

802
00:42:58,424 --> 00:43:00,952
Jadzia, daughter of Kela

803
00:43:00,997 --> 00:43:04,995
does your heart beat
only for this man?

804
00:43:05,039 --> 00:43:07,100
Yes.

805
00:43:07,144 --> 00:43:09,342
And do you swear
to join with him

806
00:43:09,383 --> 00:43:10,373
and stand with him

807
00:43:10,418 --> 00:43:12,285
against all
who would oppose you?

808
00:43:13,558 --> 00:43:15,460
I swear.

809
00:43:15,496 --> 00:43:17,694
Then let all present

810
00:43:17,734 --> 00:43:22,507
here today, know that
this man and this woman

811
00:43:22,544 --> 00:43:24,104
are married.

812
00:43:31,764 --> 00:43:32,959
Now?

813
00:43:33,001 --> 00:43:34,994
Not yet.

814
00:43:42,455 --> 00:43:43,423
Now?

815
00:43:43,457 --> 00:43:45,450
Patience.

816
00:43:47,734 --> 00:43:50,297
My Lady.

817
00:43:50,373 --> 00:43:54,474
Welcome to the House
of Martok...

818
00:43:54,515 --> 00:43:56,508
my daughter.

819
00:44:00,695 --> 00:44:01,924
Now, Doctor!

